OL,3,CSchool crossing patrollers facing
OL,4,Cabusive language and aggressive driving
OL,6,FSchool crossing patrollers in
OL,7,FBuckinghamshire are facing abusive
OL,8,Flanguage and aggressive driving, with
OL,9,Fa lollipop man saying on one occasion
OL,10,Fa motorist tried to nudge him out of
OL,11,Fthe way.
OL,13,FDavid House has been doing his job for
OL,14,Ffour years. He says he loves helping
OL,15,Ffamilies cross a busy road in
OL,16,FAylesbury but has, on occasions,
OL,17,Fwitnessed some aggressive and
OL,18,Fdangerous behaviour.
