OL,6,FThe county council is urging drivers
OL,7,Fto be respectful of those helping to
OL,8,Fkeep families and pedestrians safe as
OL,9,Fthey cross the road.
OL,11,FCllr Steven Broadbent, Deputy Leader,
OL,12,FBuckinghamshire Council, said: "It's
OL,13,Ffairly clear that people see where the
OL,14,Fcrossing is and they should slow down
OL,15,Fin a controlled manner and then wait
OL,16,Fwhile the crossing patroller has
OL,17,Ffinished and stay there in a
OL,18,Fstationary position until the crossing
OL,19,Fpatroller is back on the pavement and
OL,20,Fthey have lowered down the lollipop."
